What is SC-FC Coupling?

Structural connectivity (SC) from DTI provides the anatomical "highways" of the brain. Functional connectivity (FC) from MEG shows how regions communicate. In healthy brains, FC closely follows SC patterns (high coupling).

In SCD, functional activity may "escape" structural constraints, indicating early network dysfunction before visible atrophy.
